The project doesn't exist on disk yet, so I'll give you the config based on the path you mentioned. Since there's no `ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore` reference, I'll assume **stdio** transport (the default).

Create `.vscode/mcp.json` in your workspace root:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "MyMcpServer": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--project", "src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj"]
    }
  }
}
```

Then in VS Code:
1. Open **Copilot Chat** → switch to **Agent** mode
2. Click the **wrench icon** (Select Tools) → verify your server/tools appear
3. If tools don't appear, run `dotnet build` first and restart the server

> **If your server uses HTTP transport** (has `ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore`), use `"type": "http"` and `"url": "http://localhost:<port>"` instead.
